The Nintendo Switch 2 is here, and after spending $450 on this console, I've got some mixed feelings. Sure, it's more powerful than the original Switch, but is it really worth the premium price when you can get a Steam Deck for similar money? I put it through the ultimate test - including x-raying the internals to see what Nintendo actually improved (and what they didn't). Plus, that battery life situation is...concerning 👀
